<br>
The reason for me posting this message is that people tend to think that &quot;the grass is greener on the other side of the river&quot;. I want to give my view of things...<br>
<br>
I have spent less than 10 hours in Caledonia, both alone and in groups, both small battles and big &quot;CentralKeep&quot;-battles. <br>
Ye must remember that i am a quite young(34) troll, inexperienced and tend to get all too excited when in battle! (Argh, wrong quickbar! NOOO! I accidentally pressed &quot;Enter&quot; and typed &quot;12333121233&quot;!)<br>
I also dont have the best of gear i guess (yellow/blue ~97-100% armor, yellow admantium Great hammer, DF bracers, rings, jewel, Fire cloak etc)<br>
<br>
But our enemies dies so easily in battle! It feels great being a Skald, zooming in and out between areas. And it takes 2 enemies to kill me. (fools luck?)<br>
<br>
And i have so much more to learn!<br>
*Mez more often, more efficient and the mez CORRECT targets<br>
*Go after softer targets first, ie healers and wizards etc<br>
*Do not run like a maniac after each and every lonely enemy! The probability of meeting his/her 5 other friends around the corner is 99%!<br>
*Use strafe, all the time. Confuse them.<br>
*learn to use mouse instead of always using F8 when selecting targets (more often at least)<br>
*Protect healers, at all costs.<br>
*etc etc etc<br>
<br>
Im having a great time! Already got Master of Pain I (argh! why did i buy augmented acuity!?!?!?)! Meeting lots of realm mates, learning how to fight!<br>
<br>
And it is so much, much, much more fun to fight thinking enemies, compared to how it is in pve!!<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Philoe<br>
34 Troll Skald, Guinevere.<br>
